A legal battle over Sh2 billion assets has erupted between a woman and her father-in-law after the death of her husband. The late husband of Amina Shiraz Yakub, Jimmy Paluram Jagathram, was involved in supplying the Kenyan military with ordnance. Her father-in-law David Jagathram Baburam Melaram, a retired brigadier in the army, wants to have control his late son&rsquo;s estate.Shiraz, a chemical dependency psychologist, met her late husband at a drug rehabilitation centre in Nairobi where he had sought medical help over drug and alcohol addiction problems in 2009. Sources say Shiraz admitted Jimmy Baburam to the Karen Hospital for detoxification, but he later died of brain oedema and chronic kidney condition.